        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 3 at 5:57PM EDT until July 3 at 6:30PM EDT by NWS Upton NY</headline>
        <description>At 557 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Plainfield,
moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...70 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vehicles is possible. Expect
considerable tree damage. Wind damage is also likely to
mobile homes, roofs, and outbuildings.

This severe storm will be near...
Plainfield and Clark around 605 PM EDT.
Tottenville around 615 PM EDT.
Huguenot around 620 PM EDT.
Oakwood around 625 PM EDT.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
